        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25499",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=travisp",
                        "name": "travisp",
                        "displayName": "Travis Pew",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree that this is an issue and comes up a lot for me in unit testing, especially when param are set during dispatch.\n\nFor example:\nfunction testCreateAccount()\n{\n   $this->_login();  \/\/dispatches to \/auth\/login and logs the user in \n   $this->dispatch('\/account\/create'); \/\/any param set during the dispatch to \/auth\/login remain\n}\n\nThis is particularly a problem when an error is thrown and I want to do a second dispatch.  The ErrorHandler plugin sets the 'error_handler' param, which in some cases can cause issues.\n\nI therefore think it would make sense to have the following in Zend_Test_PHPUnit_ControllerTestCase to make it clear that this should be called.\nfunction resetRequest() {\n   $this->_request = null;\n   return $this;\n}\n\nIt would go along nicely with resetResponse, which according to the PHPdoc is 'Useful for test cases that need to test multiple trips to the server.'",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=travisp",
                        "name": "travisp",
                        "displayName": "Travis Pew",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-10-29T10:05:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-10-29T10:05:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25501",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Actually, dispatch() should simply always create a new request and response pair. (I thought I had it doing this already, but it's not.)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-10-29T10:18:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-10-29T10:18:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25771",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Added resetRequest() in r12337 and r12339.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-06T11:22:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-06T11:22:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29423",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hobodave",
                        "name": "hobodave",
                        "displayName": "David Abdemoulaie",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm reopening this due to the exact same problem being caused by the super globals being persistent across multiple requests.\n\ne.g. http:\/\/pastie.org\/private\/mpga8blwtx4gcstiplkjw\n\nIn this case, I log my user in with login(), and immediately reset the response and request. Yet, since the $_POST data still contains 'username' and 'password' values, it causes undesired behavior in my changePassword action. Obviously this is easy enough to work around now that I know what's going on. However, it's very misleading to have a resetRequest() that doesn't truly reset the request. The manual even states that these are to be used to simulate multiple requests.\n\nIf I submit two forms in a row in my browser, the data from the first doesn't linger and affect the behavior of the second :p.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hobodave",
                        "name": "hobodave",
                        "displayName": "David Abdemoulaie",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-11T16:40:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-11T16:40:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29424",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=travisp",
                        "name": "travisp",
                        "displayName": "Travis Pew",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I wanted to add that while there is a resetRequest() function now, the dispatch() function still doesn't seem to actually create the new request and response pair.  That is, I still have to call the resetRequest() and resetResponse() before any second dispatch within a single unit test.\n\nAnd to second what David said, $_POST and $_GET have to be cleared with clearPost() and clearGet(), since the newly created Request object will simply read from these.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=travisp",
                        "name": "travisp",
                        "displayName": "Travis Pew",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-11T16:48:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-11T16:48:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34493",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=duoduo",
                        "name": "duoduo",
                        "displayName": "Duo Zheng",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I am with David and Travis.\n\n$_POST and $_GET still persists. The reference guide also gives an example of this to clear POST paramaters:\n\n{code}\n$this->resetRequest()\n         ->resetResponse();\n\n$this->request->setPost(array());\n{code}\n\nThe setPost(array()) will not clear anything. resetRequest and resetResponse should handle calling clearPost() and clearGet(). If not at the very least documentation needs to updated also to use $this->request->clearPost(), but it is deceiving that resetRequest actually doesn't fully reset.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=duoduo",
                        "name": "duoduo",
                        "displayName": "Duo Zheng",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-16T11:36:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-16T11:36:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34535",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=travisp",
                        "name": "travisp",
                        "displayName": "Travis Pew",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "patch for unit tests for resetRequest() and a proposed patch to fix resetRequest()\n\nthe patch to fix resetRequest calls getRequest()->clearQuery();\nbut it could have just as easily called $_GET = array(); to fix the problem\n\nAnd I'm unsure if we also want to clear $_REQUEST. Some parts of Zend use it, but there is no method in the request object to clear the _REQUEST superglobal.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=travisp",
                        "name": "travisp",
                        "displayName": "Travis Pew",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-17T10:33:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-17T10:33:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34537",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "My own patch calls both clearQuery() and clearPost() prior to unsetting the request. \n\nResetting $_REQUEST is not a good idea, as it would also reset cookies -- which likely *should* persist between requests.\n\nMy patch will apply shortly.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-17T10:49:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-17T10:49:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34539",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed in trunk and 1.9 release branch",
